Let's create a Navbar component we can reuse in future projects.

First, we'll create a `links` object that will be used for laying things out.
```js
<script>
  export let links = [
    {
      name: 'posts',
      url: 'posts',
    },
    {
      name: 'home',
      url: '.',
    },
    {
      name: 'google',
      url: 'https://www.google.com',
    },
    {
      name: 'about',
      url: 'about',
    },
  ];
<script>
```
Then we can create our html using the links object
```html
<nav>
  <ul>
    {#each links as link}
      <li>
        <a  href={link.url}>{link.name}</a>
      </li>
    {/each}
  </ul>
</nav> 
```

